# StyleQuest — Project Context

## Environment Baseline

This is a **React Native** mobile application built on **Expo SDK 56**, **React 19**, and **TypeScript strict mode**.

Before writing or modifying platform-specific code, read the versioned Expo documentation at https://docs.expo.dev/versions/v56.0.0/.

Core dependencies and paradigms:

- **Navigation**: React Navigation v7 (`@react-navigation/native`, native-stack, bottom-tabs)
- **State**: Zustand v5 with optional persist middleware
- **Networking**: Centralized Axios client in `src/services/api/client.ts`
- **Styling**: NativeWind v4 (Tailwind) at app root; `StyleSheet.create` acceptable in components. All UI must consume **Midnight Edge** tokens from `src/config/theme.ts` — see `theme-*.mdc` rules for color, typography, and component standards.
- **Safe area**: `react-native-safe-area-context` — provider mounted in `src/App.tsx`
- **Lists**: `@shopify/flash-list` for high-performance virtualized lists
- **Animations**: `react-native-reanimated` v3+ (UI-thread worklets) + `react-native-gesture-handler` (object-based `Gesture.*` API)
- **Testing**: Jest + `jest-expo` + `@testing-library/react-native` — config in `jest.config.js`, mocks in `jest.setup.ts`
- **Path alias**: `@/*` maps to `src/*` — prefer `@/` over deep relative imports

Run `npm run typescript` after substantive TypeScript changes. Run `npm run lint` before finishing work in `src/`.

## TypeScript — Zero `any` Policy

The `any` type is **forbidden** across the entire codebase.

- Do not declare variables, parameters, return types, or generics as `any`.
- Do not use `as any` to bypass the compiler.
- Do not cast `unknown` without narrowing via type guards, `in` checks, or schema validation.
- When a type is genuinely unknown at compile time, use `unknown` and narrow before use.

```typescript
// BAD — bypasses the type system
function parsePayload(raw: any): User {
  return raw as User;
}

// GOOD — narrow before use
function parsePayload(raw: unknown): User {
  if (
    typeof raw === "object" &&
    raw !== null &&
    "id" in raw &&
    typeof (raw as Record<string, unknown>).id === "string"
  ) {
    return raw as User;
  }
  throw new Error("Invalid user payload");
}
```

Compiler options in `tsconfig.json` (`strict`, `noUncheckedIndexedAccess`, `exactOptionalPropertyTypes`) are non-negotiable. Do not weaken them.

## File Casing Policy

| Artifact | Casing | Example |
|----------|--------|---------|
| React components & screens | `PascalCase.tsx` | `HelloWorldScreen.tsx`, `ThemeProvider.tsx` |
| Custom hooks | `camelCase.ts` | `useAuth.ts`, `useDebounce.ts` |
| Utilities & services | `camelCase.ts` | `formatters.ts`, `client.ts` |
| Global constants | `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE` | `API_BASE_URL`, `STORAGE_KEYS` |

```typescript
// BAD — inconsistent constant naming
export const apiBaseUrl = "https://api.stylequest.app/v1";
export const storageKeys = { authToken: "@stylequest/auth_token" };

// GOOD — matches src/config/constants.ts conventions
export const API_BASE_URL = "https://api.stylequest.app/v1";

export const STORAGE_KEYS = {
  AUTH_TOKEN: "@stylequest/auth_token",
  USER_PROFILE: "@stylequest/user_profile",
} as const;
```

## Modularity & Layer Boundaries

Every function and module must be **abstract, self-contained, and modular**.

- Assign **one responsibility** per file. Split when a module grows beyond a single concern.
- **Components** (`src/components/`, `src/screens/`) must not import Axios, `fetch`, or Zustand stores directly — consume data through hooks (`src/hooks/`) or service modules (`src/services/`).
- **Stores** (`src/store/`) must not render UI or import React components.
- **Services** (`src/services/`) must not depend on React hooks or component lifecycle.
- **Navigation** (`src/navigation/`) must not contain business logic — delegate to hooks, stores, or services.
- Export named interfaces and types alongside implementations. Avoid default-exporting untyped objects.

```typescript
// BAD — component reaches into the data layer
import axios from "axios";
import { useAuthStore } from "@/store/authStore";

const ProfileHeader = () => {
  const token = useAuthStore((s) => s.accessToken);
  // ...
};

// GOOD — component consumes a hook abstraction
import { useAuth } from "@/hooks/useAuth";

const ProfileHeader = (): React.JSX.Element => {
  const { user } = useAuth();
  // ...
};
```

## Directory Structure

Respect the established layout:

```
src/
├── App.tsx              # Root providers (SafeAreaProvider, NavigationContainer)
├── components/          # Reusable UI building blocks
├── screens/             # Route-bound screen components
├── navigation/          # Navigators and param list types
├── hooks/               # Custom React hooks
├── store/               # Zustand slices
├── services/            # API client, storage, analytics
├── config/              # Theme, env, constants
├── types/               # Shared domain & API types
└── utils/               # Pure utility functions
```

Do not create parallel folder hierarchies or relocate modules without explicit instruction.
